          "text": "Eating protein before bed does not cause weight gain in isolation. Weight gain is determined by total caloric intake over time, not by the timing of specific meals. The 'don't eat after 7pm' rule was aimed at preventing late-night calorie overconsumption — a reasonable weight management strategy. But a targeted 30–40g protein snack before bed adds meaningful muscle-maintenance benefit without meaningfully affecting body composition if total daily calories are in check."
        }
