        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Research suggests 30–40g of protein before bed is the effective dose for men over 40 to maximize overnight muscle protein synthesis. This range accounts for anabolic resistance — the reduced muscle sensitivity to protein signals that develops with age — which means men over 40 need a slightly larger dose than younger men to trigger the same response. A cup of cottage cheese plus a small Greek yogurt gets you into this range without a large meal."
        }
      },
